This paper deals with the analysis of the IEEE 802.11 protocol in the context of wireless networks, which is a typical topic in the sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also considers the impact of transmission channel and capture effects, which are related to the physical layer of the network, and thus the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory) is also relevant. The paper uses a Markovian state transition model to analyze the behavior of the MAC layer, which is a typical approach in the sub-category of cs.MM (Modeling and Simulation). The paper also considers the impact of interference, which is related to the system-level behavior of the network, and thus the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant. Finally, the paper deals with the impact of packet transmission failures, which is related to the performance of the network, and thus the sub-category of cs.PF (Performance) is also relevant.
